data.value:
Not all students get the opportunity to dream big, and those who can, should never miss out the COMEDK examinations held in Karnataka, pursuing their higher studies. The Consortium of Medical, Engineering, and Dental Colleges of Karnataka (COMED-K) is the only exam that would land you on the flight to success. Well then, what is COMEDK? Let’s get a brief here:
COMEDK is solely responsible for determining admissions to various undergraduate and postgraduate courses, in Institutions across Karnataka. Admissions through COMEDK are based on merit lists of the candidates appearing for the examination. Since its inception, each passing year has seen an increasing number of aspirants for various disciplines like Engineering, Medical, Dental to take COMEDK entrance exams, for pursuing their graduation. COMEDK Exams is being organized to grant admissions to various private colleges in Karnataka, in a fair and transparent manner. Entire details are being published in official COMEDK website, www.comedk.org.
COMEDK generally conducts 2 different entrance examinations throughout the year, namely COMEDK PGET and COMEDK UGET.
The Under Graduate Entrance Test is being conducted by COMEDK for entrance to 12 Medical, 25 Dental and 140 Engineering colleges across Karnataka. These colleges serve approximately 8000 seats throughout Karnataka, thereby supporting a massive percentage of students aspiring for quality higher education.
Contact- COMEDK Telephone: 080-41132810 Email: # 132, Second Floor, Facsimile (Fax): 080-23568309 For PGET: pget2015@comedk.org 11th Main, 17th Cross, For UGET: uget2015@comedk.org Malleswaram, Bangalore - 560 055.
